WEBVTT

00:02.203 --> 00:03.337
[ Static ]

00:03.371 --> 00:05.673
[ Polka music plays ]

00:05.706 --> 00:08.509
♪ My dreams are all dead
and buried ♪

00:08.542 --> 00:10.644
♪ Sometimes I wish the sun
would just explode ♪

00:10.678 --> 00:12.080
♪ Just explode

00:12.113 --> 00:15.816
♪ When God comes and calls me
to his kingdom ♪

00:15.849 --> 00:18.719
♪ I'll take all you polka people
when I go ♪

00:18.752 --> 00:20.088
♪ When I go, when I go

00:20.121 --> 00:21.555
[ Yodeling ]

00:21.589 --> 00:22.990
♪ Let her blow now

00:23.023 --> 00:24.858
♪ Hey, oh
♪ Let her blow now

00:24.892 --> 00:26.327
♪ Hey, oh
♪ Let her blow now

00:26.360 --> 00:28.162
♪ Hey, oh
♪ Let her blow now

00:28.196 --> 00:29.130
♪ Hey!

00:30.431 --> 00:31.832
My turn.
Hell no.

00:31.865 --> 00:33.367
Man, let me drive that thing!
Come on.

00:33.401 --> 00:35.069
Do not touch the trim!

00:37.705 --> 00:38.872
Nubbins: As y'all know,

00:38.906 --> 00:40.741
we're gearing up
for our big mission trip.

00:40.774 --> 00:42.943
Could we please not
go to Haiti this year?

00:42.976 --> 00:45.045
We go where God calls us,
Early.

00:45.079 --> 00:46.347
Well,
if he calls from Haiti,

00:46.380 --> 00:47.881
let's don't pick up
the damn phone.

00:47.915 --> 00:49.450
'Cause I hated Haiti.
You feel me?

00:49.483 --> 00:50.851
Probably why
they call it Haiti,

00:50.884 --> 00:52.220
'cause everybody
hates it.

00:52.253 --> 00:53.221
I hate it.

00:53.254 --> 00:54.888
I had such a bad time
in Haiti.

00:54.922 --> 00:56.890
I mean, pardon my French,
but [Bleep] Haiti.

00:56.924 --> 00:58.226
Let me remind everyone --

00:58.259 --> 01:00.128
this ain't
some beach vacation.

01:00.161 --> 01:02.696
We're there to build homes
and spread the gospel.

01:02.730 --> 01:04.632
Well, I'm gonna spread
some suntan lotion,

01:04.665 --> 01:06.134
spread some legs,
spread the word

01:06.167 --> 01:08.269
that Early Cuyler's
comin' to town, baby!

01:08.302 --> 01:09.203
Unless it's Haiti.

01:09.237 --> 01:10.738
I ain't goin'
to Haiti again.

01:10.771 --> 01:13.374
We're going to
Quetzaltenango, Guatemala.

01:13.407 --> 01:14.575
Jackpot!

01:14.608 --> 01:16.744
Toes in the sand
and beer in my hand!

01:16.777 --> 01:19.380
Quetzaltenango, baby!

01:19.413 --> 01:20.714
Well, go on.

01:20.748 --> 01:21.815
Pack your swimsuit
and your boogie board.

01:21.849 --> 01:23.151
The bus leaves next Sunday.

01:23.184 --> 01:25.419
Next Sunday!
A full week from right now!

01:25.453 --> 01:27.054
Hell yeah! Whoo!

01:27.087 --> 01:29.056
[ Tires squealing
in distance ]

01:29.089 --> 01:30.424
[ Hushed voice ]
I lied, y'all.

01:30.458 --> 01:31.925
The bus leaves
tomorrow morning, 3:00 a.m.

01:31.959 --> 01:33.227
under cloak of night.

01:33.261 --> 01:35.629
But you just told Early
a week from now.

01:35.663 --> 01:37.131
And hopefully
God will forgive me,

01:37.165 --> 01:39.600
but God don't want him down
there, and neither do I.

01:39.633 --> 01:42.436
Wait, so are you leaving him
here with us?

01:42.470 --> 01:44.071
It's just a week,
Ruby Jean.

01:44.104 --> 01:45.906
Ah, don't sugarcoat it.

01:45.939 --> 01:48.309
It's the rest
of our lives!

01:48.342 --> 01:52.913
♪♪

01:52.946 --> 01:54.081
Early: Well, now...
[ Gasps ]

01:54.114 --> 01:55.949
Well,
if it ain't Jimmy Buffett

01:55.983 --> 01:57.851
setting sail
for Margaritaville.

01:57.885 --> 01:59.253
If I didn't know better,

01:59.287 --> 02:01.121
I'd say you but sneakin' off
on a mission trip.

02:01.155 --> 02:04.792
I-I just like
to be ready early, y'know.

02:04.825 --> 02:07.195
Not so early
like we're leaving early.

02:07.228 --> 02:10.030
Not like six days early
or anything.

02:10.063 --> 02:12.099
[ Chuckling ]
It ain't like we're kinda

02:12.132 --> 02:14.435
sneakin' out
under the secrecy of darkness

02:14.468 --> 02:15.936
or under the cloak of night

02:15.969 --> 02:18.506
or nothin' like that
or anything, y'know.

02:18.539 --> 02:22.743
[ Speaking Spanish ]

02:23.344 --> 02:26.347
Oh, you're learning Mexican,
are you?

02:26.380 --> 02:28.115
That's good.
Oh, yeah.

02:28.148 --> 02:29.717
I even made me
some index cards here

02:29.750 --> 02:31.319
with some common
Mexican phrases.

02:31.352 --> 02:33.321
Go on. Quiz me.

02:33.354 --> 02:35.189
"Hello."

02:35.223 --> 02:36.490
Hola.

02:36.524 --> 02:37.825
"Where is the bathroom?"

02:37.858 --> 02:39.126
Dónde está el baño.

02:39.159 --> 02:40.628
"Your breasts are plump

02:40.661 --> 02:42.230
and...sexual to me.

02:42.263 --> 02:45.666
May I pour a full gallon of milk
upon them?"

02:45.699 --> 02:47.167
Down there,
it's respectable to ask.

02:47.201 --> 02:48.836
You don't want to be
too forward.

02:48.869 --> 02:51.839
You know, this just may not
be the trip for you.

02:51.872 --> 02:53.173
Listen, I'll --
I'll see you later.

02:53.207 --> 02:56.176
I got to get to,
uh, work?

02:56.210 --> 02:57.911
You know,
what I get paid for?

02:57.945 --> 02:59.847
Uh, drivin' my police car

02:59.880 --> 03:02.049
and, uh, bein' uh,
a sheriff?

03:02.082 --> 03:04.218
Without
your gun and badge?

03:04.252 --> 03:05.319
Well, it's uh...

03:05.353 --> 03:08.689
kinda like a...
casual Monday.

03:08.722 --> 03:10.458
[ Clears throat ]
See ya later.

03:11.692 --> 03:13.694
He bought it.
[ Chuckles evilly ]

03:13.727 --> 03:16.196
[ Engine starts ] Monday's
ain't never casual.

03:16.230 --> 03:18.666
You think I don't know
corporate culture?

03:18.699 --> 03:25.172
[ Speaking Spanish ]

03:25.205 --> 03:27.541
[ Hushed voice ] Let's go.
Quick. Keep your feet movin'.

03:27.575 --> 03:28.709
Go. Go, go.

03:28.742 --> 03:29.877
Come on, Sheriff,
we got to go!

03:29.910 --> 03:30.911
I-I ran into Early.

03:30.944 --> 03:32.045
But don't worry,

03:32.079 --> 03:34.047
I'm -- I'm pretty sure
I shook him.

03:34.081 --> 03:36.116
God help me,
I told him so many lies.

03:36.149 --> 03:38.886
[ Match strikes ] Early: A
turtle of lies, would you say?

03:38.919 --> 03:42.189
Ohhh...hey, Early...
you made it.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.924
You think my boogie board's
gonna fit

03:43.957 --> 03:45.393
under that
storage compartment?

03:45.426 --> 03:47.961
Just made it last night --
Chinese gypsum.

03:47.995 --> 03:50.931
[ Strained ] Get in there,
you son of a bitch!

03:50.964 --> 03:52.300
Early, we can't
have you down there

03:52.333 --> 03:53.634
if you're
just gonna surf.

03:53.667 --> 03:56.136
I know that.
I'm also scuba diving.

03:57.438 --> 03:59.407
I'm ready to explore
the briny deep!

03:59.440 --> 04:02.042
I got you a new
[grunting] toothbrush!

04:02.075 --> 04:05.746
You got to keep them
pearly whites sparkly clean!

04:05.779 --> 04:08.282
You think I'm some kind of fool?
[ Thwack! ]

04:08.316 --> 04:10.384
If I get back
from preaching Jesus' word

04:10.418 --> 04:12.420
and I find out you been
[bleep] with me,

04:12.453 --> 04:14.488
you been [bleep]
the damn wrong [bleep]hole.

04:14.522 --> 04:17.425
I will burn that goddamn house
to the ground

04:17.458 --> 04:19.092
with every damn one of us
in it.

04:19.126 --> 04:21.194
You get my message?

04:21.795 --> 04:23.331
Now give me
my damn toothbrush.

04:23.364 --> 04:24.765
Okay, love you!
I love you, Daddy.

04:24.798 --> 04:25.766
I love you too, son!

04:25.799 --> 04:26.967
Now, preacher,

04:27.000 --> 04:29.437
I expect to have
the same itinerary

04:29.470 --> 04:30.671
as everybody else.

04:30.704 --> 04:33.140
Fine. Fine,
here you go, big man.

04:33.173 --> 04:36.076
Buildin' houses?
6:00 a.m.?

04:36.109 --> 04:38.812
Who made this son-of-a-bitch
vacation schedule?

04:40.147 --> 04:43.651
♪ Kumbaya, my lord

04:43.684 --> 04:45.786
♪ Kumbaya

04:45.819 --> 04:47.120
I thought
we was buildin' a wall

04:47.154 --> 04:48.188
to keep 'em out --

04:48.221 --> 04:49.957
not four walls
and a roof!

04:49.990 --> 04:51.792
God damn,
it's hot out here!

04:51.825 --> 04:53.961
What kind of dumb-ass people
live in a place this hot?!

04:53.994 --> 04:56.830
♪ Kumbaya, my lord What happened
to "America First," huh?

04:56.864 --> 04:59.132
♪ Kumbaya Hell, I got holes in
my own son-of-a-bitchin' roof!

04:59.166 --> 05:00.501
If I wanted
to work on a house,

05:00.534 --> 05:02.135
I could've stayed home
and done that!

05:02.169 --> 05:03.871
You think I like
workin' on houses?

05:03.904 --> 05:07.007
Hell, no!
My house is a piece of shit!

05:07.040 --> 05:08.141
Rusty:
Hey, Granny, look at this.

05:08.175 --> 05:09.477
I found all these samples

05:09.510 --> 05:11.545
in the dumpster
behind the paint store.

05:11.579 --> 05:12.980
Oh, it's beautiful, baby.

05:13.013 --> 05:15.816
Like Joseph's
coat of many colors.

05:15.849 --> 05:17.485
Sure is nice not having

05:17.518 --> 05:20.220
that old damn
third wheel around.

05:20.253 --> 05:22.556
You know, sometimes,
squeaky wheels,

05:22.590 --> 05:24.124
they get greased.

05:24.157 --> 05:25.659
"Woman, please, no!"

05:25.693 --> 05:27.027
[ Gunshot ]
[ Chuckles ]

05:27.060 --> 05:28.161
Granny, come on, now.

05:28.195 --> 05:29.563
You know
no one would blame us.

05:29.597 --> 05:30.664
Whoop--

05:30.698 --> 05:32.199
[ Gunshot ]
Gimme that.

05:32.232 --> 05:34.167
Listen, I think Daddy's
gonna come back a changed man

05:34.201 --> 05:35.335
after spending some time
down there

05:35.369 --> 05:36.504
and spreadin'
the gospel.

05:36.537 --> 05:38.739
I hope he's spreadin'
his ass cheeks

05:38.772 --> 05:40.641
in the Guatemalan jail.

05:40.674 --> 05:41.975
♪♪

05:42.009 --> 05:43.210
Sheriff: Hoo-whee!

05:43.243 --> 05:47.014
Stick a fork in me,
ha, I'm done.

05:47.047 --> 05:49.683
Early, will you pray
in fellowship with me?

05:49.717 --> 05:52.052
God damn it, ain't we talked
to him enough today?

05:54.722 --> 05:55.856
Blessed Jesus,

05:55.889 --> 05:57.591
I thank thee
for the opportunity

05:57.625 --> 05:59.226
to build houses down here,

05:59.259 --> 06:01.695
even though I claim to be
a master electrician,

06:01.729 --> 06:05.566
and you and I both know,
very well, that I am not.

06:05.599 --> 06:08.502
Please allow us
safe passage back to America,

06:08.536 --> 06:12.440
where the food doesn't give me
such explosive diarrhea.

06:12.473 --> 06:14.875
[ To the tune of "Kumbaya" ]
♪ Copper pipes, my lord

06:14.908 --> 06:17.878
♪ Copper wire

06:17.911 --> 06:19.880
♪ Head to town, my Lord

06:19.913 --> 06:21.682
♪ Find a buyer

06:21.715 --> 06:24.051
I mean, half the time
when I squat over

06:24.084 --> 06:26.053
one of these holes
in the ground,

06:26.086 --> 06:28.288
I -- I mess
right in my pants

06:28.321 --> 06:30.223
'cause I can't get
no leverage.

06:30.257 --> 06:31.925
♪ Tie one on, my lord

06:31.959 --> 06:33.393
♪ And drink some drinks

06:33.427 --> 06:34.962
♪ Get [cha-ching] up,
my lord ♪

06:34.995 --> 06:37.230
♪ Cause hijinks
Whoo!

06:37.264 --> 06:39.567
Lord, I only packed
seven pairs of undies

06:39.600 --> 06:41.635
and I've fully wrecked
six of them.

06:41.669 --> 06:44.071
Why would you create
such a place?

06:44.104 --> 06:47.975
Anyway, I should
wrap this up, so...amen.

06:48.008 --> 06:49.142
What the --?

06:49.176 --> 06:51.411
His boogie board.
His note cards.

06:51.445 --> 06:53.080
Everything
he would have with him

06:53.113 --> 06:54.815
if he were leaving, gone.

06:54.848 --> 06:58.018
[ Latin club music playing ]

07:07.495 --> 07:08.762
Yeah, baby!

07:08.796 --> 07:10.564
Let's get some leche
up in here in this bitch!

07:10.598 --> 07:12.165
Somebody's gonna
finally let me do it!

07:12.199 --> 07:14.502
Hell yeah! Owww!

07:14.535 --> 07:15.636
Señorita?

07:15.669 --> 07:16.637
[ Cow moos ]

07:16.670 --> 07:18.271
[ Men grunting ]

07:18.305 --> 07:21.174
Sheriff: The copper pipes.
The copper wires.

07:21.208 --> 07:23.243
Everything Early
would probably

07:23.276 --> 07:25.145
rip off of
a job site, gone.

07:25.178 --> 07:26.614
Unbelievable.

07:26.647 --> 07:27.748
Don't I know it.

07:27.781 --> 07:28.749
[ Spits ]

07:28.782 --> 07:30.183
The crime down here sucks.

07:30.217 --> 07:32.019
Where are all the pipes,
Early?

07:32.052 --> 07:33.320
What you mean
"all the pipes"?

07:33.353 --> 07:34.855
There's still some PVC
up there.

07:34.888 --> 07:36.824
'Cause nobody wants PVC!

07:36.857 --> 07:38.025
Ooh, but they go crazy

07:38.058 --> 07:39.493
for that copper though,
won't they?

07:39.527 --> 07:41.094
Whoo! The market for that
is robust!

07:41.128 --> 07:43.296
I knew it was you.
Drive him to the airstrip...

07:43.330 --> 07:44.965
Whoa, whoa!
Hey, wait, wait!

07:44.998 --> 07:46.967
...and put him on a flight home.
You the same sombitches

07:47.000 --> 07:48.301
that beat my ass
three hours ago!

07:48.335 --> 07:50.303
[ Wailing ]
Corruption!

07:51.338 --> 07:53.541
Early: Landscaping...
paint job...

07:53.574 --> 07:56.109
Looks nice what y'all done
with the place.

07:56.143 --> 07:58.979
Gon' look even better
all lit up at night...

07:59.012 --> 08:00.180
on fire.

08:00.213 --> 08:02.215
Aww.
You just got home.

08:02.249 --> 08:04.685
Why not kick back
and relax,

08:04.718 --> 08:07.955
and not say all that
ominous, terrifying shit

08:07.988 --> 08:09.356
for a little bit?

08:09.389 --> 08:11.124
What do you -- what do you mean
light it on fire?

08:11.158 --> 08:12.325
So they won't think
it was me.

08:12.359 --> 08:14.628
So they don't know
what I'm doin',

08:14.662 --> 08:17.197
or what I done,
or what I plan to do!

08:17.230 --> 08:20.000
Yeah, I still don't know
what your doin'.

08:20.033 --> 08:21.535
Or what you done.

08:21.569 --> 08:23.336
Or what you're
plannin' to do, Daddy.

08:23.370 --> 08:25.172
I'm sayin', if it was me,

08:25.205 --> 08:27.207
how did my house
burn down too?

08:27.240 --> 08:29.877
Thus there's not a way
it was me.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.244
To do what?

08:31.278 --> 08:33.313
To burn
the goddamn church down

08:33.346 --> 08:36.016
for how they hurt
my damn feelings down there.

08:36.049 --> 08:38.385
If in fact
that is what I did,

08:38.418 --> 08:41.555
which is not what I did,
'cause I didn't do it!

08:44.257 --> 08:46.359
Rusty: Daddy, why do we always
got to solve our problems

08:46.393 --> 08:47.695
by burnin' the house down?

08:47.728 --> 08:49.196
Didn't I just
go over this?

08:49.229 --> 08:51.064
It's like we don't
communicate no more!

08:51.098 --> 08:52.099
[ Glass shatters ]

08:52.132 --> 08:54.267
♪♪

08:54.301 --> 08:56.236
[ Grunting ]
There we go.

08:56.269 --> 08:59.372
Bienvenidos
to your new casa.

08:59.406 --> 09:03.010
[ Electricity crackles ]

09:03.043 --> 09:04.377
Ohh, Sheriff.

09:04.411 --> 09:06.513
Look, I prayed
that this would work,

09:06.546 --> 09:08.949
and now I'm prayin'
for forgiveness.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.718
Can we all join hands?

09:10.751 --> 09:14.454
Come on, y'all,
we got a flight to catch.

09:18.659 --> 09:20.227
Well, you know, Satan,
he's --

09:20.260 --> 09:22.963
he also works in
mysterious ways too.

09:22.996 --> 09:24.231
Oh,
you're a preacher now?

09:24.264 --> 09:26.099
'Cause you certainly
ain't an electrician.

09:26.133 --> 09:27.234
What the hell?!

09:27.267 --> 09:28.902
Our sanctuary!

09:28.936 --> 09:29.903
Put it out!

09:29.937 --> 09:31.104
Everybody put it out!

09:31.138 --> 09:32.873
Ah, don't worry,
Pastor Nubbins.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.242
Maybe some Guatemalans
will fly up here,

09:35.275 --> 09:36.910
with fancy t-shirts on,

09:36.944 --> 09:38.245
and rebuild you a church.

09:38.278 --> 09:40.213
Early, what the hell
are you doing here?

09:40.247 --> 09:42.415
When y'all sent me home
the way you done,

09:42.449 --> 09:44.551
every voice in my head
was a-tellin' me,

09:44.584 --> 09:46.286
"burn that damn church down

09:46.319 --> 09:48.756
and then burn
your own house down, too,

09:48.789 --> 09:50.423
so they won't think
you done it."

09:50.457 --> 09:52.325
But I didn't
burn this church down.

09:52.359 --> 09:54.261
Because I was raised
better than that.

09:54.294 --> 09:56.429
This here
was done by lightning.

09:56.463 --> 09:57.998
Lightning?
Uh-huh.

09:58.031 --> 09:59.432
Lightning strike.

09:59.466 --> 10:01.434
Straight from
Jesus' fingertips, probably.

10:01.468 --> 10:03.771
You know how he hates for me
to get my feelings hurt.

10:03.804 --> 10:05.906
For some reason,
I don't believe you, Early.

10:05.939 --> 10:08.441
Hell, how could I be lying?
It hit my place too.

10:08.475 --> 10:10.744
Your place burned too,
Early?

10:10.778 --> 10:12.579
Well,
there's no way he's lying.

10:12.612 --> 10:13.947
And Sheriff
ain't lying neither.

10:13.981 --> 10:16.116
His place burned, as well.
What?!

10:16.149 --> 10:17.785
Momma!
[ Whining ] No!

10:17.818 --> 10:20.320
Looks like the Christ child
is smiting you all

10:20.353 --> 10:21.588
for all the hubris
of what --

10:21.621 --> 10:23.356
[ Gunshot ]
Oh, my God!

10:23.390 --> 10:25.292
Early!
Oh, no!

10:25.325 --> 10:28.528
My only boy, struck
down in his prime! Oh!

10:28.561 --> 10:30.698
Uh...
By lightning.

10:30.731 --> 10:32.632
Lightning got him,
right?

10:32.666 --> 10:34.434
I mean, there's no question.
Lightning.

10:34.467 --> 10:35.602
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.
-Yeah.

10:35.635 --> 10:36.804
-Yeah.
-Looked like lightning.

10:36.837 --> 10:38.638
It looked like
you kinda shot --

10:38.672 --> 10:40.140
[ Gunshot ] My knee!
[ Whimpers ]

10:40.173 --> 10:42.676
Lightning can hit anyone.

10:42.710 --> 10:45.813
Anyone...

10:45.846 --> 10:48.115
I'll just write it up
as lightning.

10:48.148 --> 10:56.023
♪♪

10:56.056 --> 11:03.964
♪♪

11:03.997 --> 11:11.939
♪♪
